Iteration One
\ 0$ = free as null \
\ 1$ = source Ptr \
\ 2$ = source length \
\ 3$ = instr Ptr \
\ 4$ = instr length \
\ 5$ = output Ptr \

2 = 1$ : 0 = 1$I : 0 = 1$S : \ (3) Ptr to source  \
1 = 3$ : 0 = 3$I : 0 = 3$S : \ (3) Ptr to instr 0 \
1 = 5$ : 0 = 5$I : 0 = 5$S : \ (3) Ptr to output  \
\ at 10 = -4 jump back, for each line after 10 jump back one less (so if 11 lines, jump back -5) \

\ iterate over source \
1$ => 3$I : \ target the column for the char \

0 = 3$S : \ instr iterator lands here and zero instr Ptr subindex \

3$ <=> 5$ : \ extract the instruction out \
1 + 3$S : \ increment the char instr index and the output index \
1 + 5$S : 
3$S L 4$ :
-5 C :

1 + 1$S :
1$S L 2$  : \ keep going until it's equal to 1$ (our iteration ammount) \
-10 C : 



